##These Wuhan War pestilence core"small person", unexpectedly recognized each other after the mask in"dictation record"

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Delivery boy, barber, medical staff, patients... in the anti-epidemic front of each "little people" meet and Reunion, are a vivid story. They are the grains of history that we pick up and shine in the sun.

By Wu Xue

On an ordinary weekday evening, the News Editor Group suddenly received a message: "I was reading your Wuhan delivery boy, and the contents of a nurse's diary collected by me were matched by master Gan. " The senior editor of the weekly, the master Gan, was speaking, in the February 15 issue of dictation | delivery boy to fix the Golden Pool of medical problems: I do not send a courier, is the life of the people.
In an article published on February 15th, "delivery boy" , Ganshi is cutting hair for medical staff

In the photo, Ganshi appears with a photo of him cutting hair. He is skillful because he wears a mask and can not see his face clearly. In the "diary of a nurse" , there is the following description of Master Gan: "today, a good barber of master Gan, gave up the rest time, rushed to the hotel to serve you. "
More coincidentally, in February 13 to promote the "war" "epidemic" Vanguard Driving Wuhan, Shanghai can hold it? " Article, Master Gan actually already wearing blue protective clothing on camera.
Who is master Gan, why appear frequently in the mouth of nurse, doctor, volunteer.

After many twists and turns, I finally got in touch with master Gan. The handset of his mobile phone is also broken, it turns out that these days from the major hospitals voluntary haircuts, frequently caused by alcohol disinfection. During the day, master Gan had to receive forty medical staff. He couldn't spare the time to give an interview. He made three appointments before and after, and finally found time at 8 pm.
Don't say, master Gan has a head of curly personality, experience is also quite legendary.
Ganshushuang is the full name of Ganshushuang, a native of Wuhan. At 14, he became a Barber's apprentice; four years ago, he applied for a job as an ambulance driver at Wuhan No. 1 Hospital and opened a barber shop near the hospital. Today, he has another identity -- as a hairdresser. On January 31, master Gan happened to brush up on a recruitment notice in a circle of friends: "Urgent Barber, for the medical and nursing staff in Wuhan. ".
Master Kam cuts the hair of female doctors

Master Gan told me that since January 22, he has been responsible for transferring patients to eight designated hospitals in Wuhan First Hospital. In an emergency, he can transfer more than 20 patients a day. Until the first day of the New Year, began to do a break two. Because in the transfer process, master Gan himself also wear protective clothing, wear a hat, know long hair is particularly inconvenient, but also easy to cross-infection. Master Gan has always wanted to use his "second break" time to do something practical.
"I never found the channel, saw the recruitment information, and volunteered. " After a simple docking inquiry, soon, master Gan was pulled into the volunteer group, got to know Wang Yong and several other volunteers, the same day on the "start. ". The first haircut was to the Guanggu district of Wuhan's Third People's Hospital. Volunteers drove master Gan to his destination. The team leader who received him, named Weng Chao, was the head of the Sensory Department of the East Hospital of Shanghai Yangpu District, is also the Shanghai Second Aid Han Medical Team Material Logistics Support Group leader.
Master Gan set off to the hospital for a haircut in protective clothing

"On the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, many people are casually cut, can not find a place to cut. " Weng Chao said this is no way things. Master Gan has been here three times and usually arrives at 9 am on the DOT, working until 7 pm or later. As for hairstyles, boys cut board inches, girls cut short hair, or hair tied up, the back of the head from the push-off, easy to manage. The scope of service includes Wuhan Sanyuan, Jinyintan Hospital, Wuhan First Hospital and other hospitals as well as the national medical team in Wuhan.
In master Gan's opinion, a haircut is not just a haircut, the process of haircut is a relaxing process. Because he was on the front line of medical treatment, he especially understood the pressure of medical treatment on medical staff. He chatted with them about life in Shanghai, customs in Wuhan and even some interesting stories between the "Click Click Click" of scissors, can loosen their tight strings for a while. After the first "start" , Ganshi do not want to trouble volunteers again to transport, once the hospital has the need for hairdressing, choose their own drive to and from the hospital.
Master Gan is cutting the hair of the medical staff

After cutting his hair, master Gan took a photo with the medical staff

On February 16, Wuhan saw a sudden drop in temperature and heavy snow. As usual, master Gan went to Wuhan Sanyuan to work, suddenly found that the battery of the van ran out. Sealed city, close the door, at this stage simply can not find people and places to repair the car, master Gan will be a man with his bare hands to push the van sliding 20 meters away, after reaching a slope, with the sliding impact ignited the engine. At 9 o'clock in the morning, master Gan appeared at Wuhan Sanyuan on time. Weng Chao said when he saw him, "Oh, it's so cold and on time. Thank you. "
Weng Chao, though not in the news, has much to do with Wang Yong. As the head of the Logistics Support Group of Wuhan Sanyuan, Weng Chao is responsible for the purchase of life materials and medical materials for all the people in the medical team. In the "delivery boy" article, Wang Yong once helped the Shanghai medical team buy a birthday cake, and the recipient was Weng Chao.
"We had just come to Wuhan, and we didn't know each other very well. The team members were working hard day and night. I wanted to hold a little birthday ceremony for the team members for their recent birthdays to relieve their pressure, " said Weng Chao, he remembered that the cake was very small, 6 inches. The paramedics couldn't blow out the candles with masks on. They made a gesture of blowing out the candles when they took the picture. Finally, the candles were put out by hand, "I think it's a memory that all of us will remember for the rest of our lives. ".
The Shanghai medical team put out the candles with their hands

Weng Chao said with emotion that another thing that impressed him was Wang Yong's help. The traditional shoe covers from Shanghai were too short to be protective, so he had to find longer ones quickly. He asked Wang Yong for help. Wang readily agreed, and within two days they were in Weng's hands. "I didn't know how he got it, " said Weng. "after reading the article, I realized that all of Wuhan was out of stock. Wang Yong pulled back 2,000 pairs overnight at a GE store Taobao store in Ezhou, 55 kilometers from the city. I really think he's very difficult."
Wang Yong, the delivery guy

In fact, those who appeared in the weekly's tweets as frequently as Ganshi included Dr. Zhang Yihui from the Shanghai Hospital and Zhan Xin, a patient who was hospitalized at the time.
In the Feb. 10 issue of the dictation | "as long as one of US lives, our 5-year-old daughter will not be an orphan, " I relied on this belief to carry me to victory, a photo of Zhang Yihui, a member of Shanghai's Fourth Academy, taking throat swabs from patients in Wuhan is seamlessly linked to another article, "the most beautiful retrograde person whose real name is given as an example. ".
Although the picture only saw the back, but "Dr. Baymax" serious action, is so familiar and kind.
The photos of Zhang Yihui and the patient were seamlessly linked in two weekly reports

The couple, whose wife, Zhan Xin, was photographed taking a throat swab test, were interviewed orally. On the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, Zhang Yihui, director of the Respiratory Department of the Shanghai Fourth People's Hospital, led 15 medical staff to form a team of Hubei medical team to support the three hospitals in Wuhan. Zhan Xin was one of the first patients they took over.
On the first day of his visit, Zhang recalled, the hospital had already admitted more than 350 patients to its designated 350 beds, and medical staff had been working through the night, almost without a break. After the medical team took over, they were able to have a short rest. As the head of Ward 17, Zhang's first act was to put himself in the most dangerous position in the ward: a throat swab operation for nucleic acid testing for all new crown patients.
Zhan Xin is the patient of 39 bed, when come, fever abated but have a little cough, in the mind still have some fear. Shen Yanmei, a nurse in charge of the Rehabilitation Hospital affiliated to Tongji University, who is in charge of bed management, and the two of them are very similar in age. Shen Yanmei often comforted her by saying, "This is a mild case. Relax and you will be fine. " In order not to increase the burden on the patients, Zhang Yihui, he chose medication based on his symptoms. Nurses will also set up a "doctor-patient exchange group, " even if not in the post, but also 24 hours to answer patients' concerns and questions. February 7, Zhan new fever three days, nucleic acid test twice negative, recovered from the hospital.
Zhan Xin poses with Shen Yanmei, a nurse in charge at the Tongji University

On the day of discharge from hospital, the three hospitals in Wuhan held a small ceremony for seven of the first batch of patients who had recovered. Zhan Xin danced excitedly. She picked up her mobile phone and took this picture with Shen Yanmei, and said with a smile: "Wait until the spring flowers come to Wuhan, please eat Wuhan Duck Neck Ah. "
According to the current "should receive receive" principle, Zhang Yihui's ward admitted 58 patients, far more than the designated bed 35, "the additional beds are filled, but we are in a good state of mind.
Delivery boy, barber, medical staff, patients... in the anti-epidemic front of each "little people" meet and Reunion, are a vivid story. They are the grains of history that we pick up and shine in the sun.
The pictures in this article are provided by the interviewees
